- How JCL compilation process works:
		1. When JCL code is submitted, before going into JES (Job Entry Subsystem) it is converted in interpreted text that can be understood by JES, and stored under dataset called SPOOL.
		2. Then JES checks the job priority based on the CLASS and PRTY parameters.
		3. Then JCL synatx errs are checked and if no errors are there then JOB is scheduled into JOB queue.
		4. Once the job is loaded in JOB queue, it is sent for job execution based on input file and the log is created into the spool.

