- Diff b/w CATLG and UNCATLG
	Catalog:
		Cataloging a dataset means registering its information in the system catalog.
		Once a dataset is cataloged, the system can easily locate it using just its dataset name (DSN).
		Cataloging is useful because it simplifies dataset management; the system knows the physical location of the dataset without needing manual intervention.
	Uncatalog:
		Uncataloging a dataset means removing its reference from the system catalog, but the physical dataset remains on disk.
		Once a dataset is uncataloged, the system no longer knows its location, and the dataset cannot be accessed by simply referring to its DSN. However, if the physical location (volume/track) is known, it can still be accessed manually.

- What does the TIME parameter signify ? What does TIME=1440 mean ?
	TIME parameter can be used to overcome S322 abends for programs that genuinely need more CPU time. TIME=1440 means no CPU time limit is to be applied to this step.

- What is COND=EVEN?
	It means execute this step even if any of the previous steps, terminated abnormally.

- What is COND=ONLY?
	It means execute this step only if any of the previous steps, terminated abnormally.

- When you want to execute the step anyhow?
	COND=(0,GT) | COND=(4095,LT) 

- When you dont want to execute the step?
	COND=(0,LT) | COND=(4095,GT)

